ef="https://www.nme.com/artists/tablo">Tablo</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/big-bang">Big Bang</a>的<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/taeyang">Taeyang</a>等。</p><p>在其他 BTS 新闻中， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-kid-laroi-too-much-bts-jungkook-central-cee-3511644">The Kid Laroi 和 Jungkook 最近合作了歌曲“Too Much”</a> ，其中也有<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/central-cee">Central Cee</a>的参与。这首歌预计将出现在这位澳大利亚歌手即将于 11 月发行的首张录音室专辑“The First Time”中。</p><p>与此同时，柾国也将于下个月发行他的首张录音室专辑《Golden》。该项目将与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/dj-snake">DJ Snake</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/major-lazer">Major Lazer</a>等艺术家<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/bts-jungkook-golden-tracklist-collaboration-major-lazer-dj-snake-3515560">进行一系列备受瞩目的合作</a>。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/shinee-taemin-to-guest-star-on-bts-suga-talk-show-suchwita-3520933">SHINee 泰民客串 BTS Suga 脱口秀节目《Suchwita》的消息</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
 Yard Act 分享《Dream Job》并介绍新专辑《Where's My Utopia？》：“这是关于希望和毅力的” https://www.nme.com/news/music/yard-act-interview-james-smith-dream-job-wheres-my-utopia-new-album-3520645?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=yard-act-采访詹姆斯史密斯梦想工作在哪里我的乌托邦新专辑Andrew TrendellWed, 25 Oct 2023 09:00:56 +0000 Music InterviewsMusic NewsNewsIndie https://www.nme.com/?p=3520645 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="庭院法案，2023 年。图片来源：Phoebe Fox" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>主唱詹姆斯·史密斯讲述了他们第二张专辑的“派对”，以及“非常荣幸但也很挣扎”的挣扎</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/yard-act-interview-james-smith-dream-job-wheres-my-utopia-new-album-3520645">Yard Act 后分享“Dream Job”并告诉我们新专辑“Where&#39;s My Utopia？”：“It&#39;s about Hope and Perseverance”</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="庭院法案，2023 年。图片来源：Phoebe Fox" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two_landscape_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/yard-act">Yard Act</a>分享了新单曲“Dream Job”以及第二张专辑“Where&#39;s My Utopia？”的详细信息。以及一场盛大的返校节表演。请查看下面的全部内容以及我们对主唱詹姆斯·史密斯的采访。</p><p>这支利兹乐队广受赞誉的 2022 年水星奖提名首张专辑《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/yard-act-the-overload-review-radar-3140683">The Overload</a> 》的后续作品将于 2024 年 3 月 1 日推出，第一首试听歌曲将是自我分析但可跳舞的《Where&#39;s My Utopia？》 – 史密斯在其中与“非常荣幸但也很挣扎”的感觉作斗争，以成为一支成功的乐队。</p><p> “《Dream Job》在专辑的叙事弧线中途到来，但它接续了乐队去年年底停下来的地方，当时我终于有时间思考发生在我们身上的一切，”史密斯告诉<em>NME</em> 。 “人们总是问，‘哦，你已经实现了这一切——感觉如何？’但当场很难说清楚。</p><p> “我了解到，我必须对自己和周围的人撒谎才能度过难关，但这不一定是坏事——这是一种应对策略。我所说的一切都是事实；它是王牌，它是顶级，它是老板，它是一流的，以及我用来描述我们所经历的这段旅程和我所从事的这份工作的所有其他最高级的词。”</p><p>他继续说道：“而且，事情没那么简单。去做你从青少年时期就想做的事情并不能真正解决你的问题。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="院子法案 - 梦想工作" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Pc5t9m2Hg9c?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>这张专辑由乐队与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/gorillaz">Gorillaz</a>成员 Remi Kabaka Jr. 共同制作，并将在 2024 年英国和欧洲大型巡演中推出，其中包括 8 月 3 日在利兹千禧广场举行的大型返校演出。</p><p>在度过了一个盛夏之后，他们<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/yard-act-shout-out-sam-fender-and-bring-out-the-dancers-to-open-main-stage-at-reading-2023-3488648">在雷丁音乐节上打开了主舞台</a>，推出了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-yard-act-self-referential-new-single-the-trench-coat-museum-3468239">一次性单曲“风衣博物馆</a>”，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/yard-act-harry-hill-leeds-interview-trench-coat-army-new-album-3447052">在布鲁德内尔社交俱乐部进行了五晚的驻场表演，并附上了一张喜剧演员的支持卡</a>，乐队仍然挤满了人。计划在第二个记录周期出现之前看到 2023 年。</p><p>我们采访了主唱詹姆斯·史密斯。</p><h3><strong>你好詹姆斯。 “我的乌托邦在哪里？”的主题是得到你想要的一切，但感觉不太对劲，这确实是一个非常普遍的主题，对吧？</strong></h3><p><strong>史密斯：</strong> “是的。这就是人类激励自己度过这一天的方式：认为还有更好的东西。对我来说，在我的整个成年生活中，我的很大一部分对找到爱情和生孩子感到非常满意——这是专辑的另一个重要元素——但我的另一部分非常确定，这就是我想要的。通缉。我确实对所发生的一切感到非常高兴，但这是一段旅程和一场斗争。过去的两年经历了很多，我没有时间去处理正在发生的事情。事后我对此了解了更多。</p><p> “即使在早期的谈话中，当我开始告诉乐队我在写什么时，他们也会说，‘哦，你在写一个成功的乐队有多难？这件事不会顺利进行，詹姆斯……”</p><h3><strong>但这是为了追逐彩虹尽头的那一桶金吗？</strong></h3><p> “这是关于希望和毅力。我们一直以来所做的很多事情都是植根于社会所处的位置和对时代的评论，但它更具有普遍性。人类始终被我们的野心所驱动。在一个目前有超市可以买到食物、有房子可以居住的世界里，一旦我们掌握了基本知识，我们就会渴望其他我们认为重要的东西，因为我们不满足于仅仅成为动物。 ”</p><h3><strong>专辑中还有其他关键歌词或时刻可以说明这一点吗？</strong></h3><p> “《The Undertow》中有一句话，这是我控制自己的口头禅： <em>“我们都被自己的观点所束缚，任何低于我们自己的低点我们永远不会真正知道”</em> 。这就是我对自己说的，你的挣扎和情绪是你自己的，你完全有权感受你所感受到的一切，但这并不反映任何人，也不能与除了你自己之外的任何人进行比较。</p><p> “我常常对自己的感受不屑一顾，因为人们比我更挣扎。尤其是当这件事发生的时候。 “人们会为了处于这个位置而杀人。你怎么敢不享受它呢？生活的二元性在于，你自己的个人观点和其他人的观点是两个独立的事物。两种感觉都很好；你很幸运，但也很挣扎。” </p><figure id="attachment_3520647" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3520647" style="width: 1066px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3520647" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two.jpeg" alt="庭院法案，2023 年。图片来源：Phoebe Fox" width="1066" height="1600" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two.jpeg 1066w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two-400x600.jpeg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two-800x1201.jpeg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_album_two-696x1045.jpeg 696w" sizes="(max-width: 1066px) 100vw, 1066px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3520647" class="wp-caption-text">庭院法案，2023 年。图片来源：Phoebe Fox</figcaption></figure><h3><strong>关于<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pressure-cooker-impact-of-touring-on-mental-health-needs-addressing-but-help-is-at-hand-3512555">巡演的压力</a>已经说了很多——没有人能够真正洞察或理解你自己的小宇宙。</strong></h3><p> “不，他们不能。我已经戒酒了，这对我有很大帮助。我在记录中提到过几次。对我来说，问题在于问自己更想要什么：一半的时间一半的时间，或者能够尽自己最大的能力完成你一直想做的工作。为了充分利用它，我必须戒酒。这对我来说是一件非常深刻和令人振奋的事情。</p><p> “当你去美国和欧洲，回到较小的场所时，会有很多人主动请你喝一杯，然后当你说你不喝酒时​​，他们会当着你的面嘲笑你，这真是太疯狂了。就像，“我不能每天晚上都这样做，否则我会死的！”我从很远的地方直面现实，决定做出选择。你来这里是为了参加聚会，你是为了娱乐。尽管它是一种创造性的表达，但它也是一种娱乐。你必须扮演这个角色，但你不能每晚都扮演那个角色。如此频繁地重复，真是太疯狂了。”</p><h3><strong>这融入了这张专辑苦乐参半的本质。从声音上来说，这是一张派对唱片，对吧？</strong></h3><p> “是的。我还是喜欢聚会。如果到了紧要关头，迪斯科是我最喜欢的音乐，因为我喜欢跳舞。我们是一支充满幽默感的乐队，这张专辑里也充满了幽默感。我们不会为了解决我们所遇到的问题而删除生活中我们喜欢的东西。</p><p> “历史上很多我喜爱的乐队都成功地做到了这两点。在让痛苦变得可口方面，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/THE-CURE">治愈者</a>是这方面的王者。但这并不是痛苦；而是痛苦。这很复杂。这是一张派对专辑，我们制作它非常有趣。在音乐上，感觉真的很自由。我们不觉得被任何东西束缚。我们互相推搡。我们听各种音乐以及唱片中的音乐。我们有时间和空间说，“那为什么不能创作一首非洲节奏风格的歌曲呢？”我们听了很多 Fela Kuti 之类的东西，那么为什么我们不展示我们的这一面并将其变成一首关于布莱克浦的歌曲呢？这大概是你能到达的离非洲最远的地方了。</p><p> “这里面有一个笑话。 Shippo [Sam Shipstone，吉他手] 将非洲节拍节奏带到了这个吉他系列中，我正在考虑要写些什么。当我想到布莱克浦时，我发现这本身就很滑稽。你得想办法让自己高兴起来。” </p><figure id="attachment_3488655" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3488655" style="width: 1500px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3488655" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1.jpg" alt="雷丁 2023 年《庭院法案》。图片来源：Andy Ford for NME" width="1500" height="1000" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1.jpg 1500w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1-400x267.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1-696x464.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1-1392x928.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Reading23_NME_YARDACT_AFord-60441-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3488655" class="wp-caption-text">雷丁 2023 年《庭院法案》。图片来源：Andy Ford for NME</figcaption></figure><h3> <strong>《An Illusion》带有一丝嘻哈气息，《The Undertow》感觉就像是 Groovejet 与 Studio 54 的结合，而《Petroleum》的结尾则有工业风。这不是后朋克唱片，是吗？</strong></h3><p> “我真的希望每个人都同意事实并非如此，因为我们已经超越了这一点，我希望其他人也能看到这一点。如果评论只是说“听起来又像是<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/THE-FALL">秋天</a>了”，我会感到沮丧。他们会说这听起来像‘打北’……”</p><h3><strong>你是否因为感觉太后朋克而扔掉了很多东西？</strong></h3><p> “不，它根本没有意识。第一张专辑也不是有意识地被写成后朋克专辑，只是我们使用了最少的乐器。 We were influenced by <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/gang-of-four">Gang Of Four</a> and The Fall and stuff obviously, but there were a lot of other influences on the first album that were in the background but we weren&#39;t quite there yet as a unit. &#39;The Overload&#39; was written quite remotely and quite quickly without much thought. Whereas this has been sprawling by comparison, it&#39;s been written by the four of us, and we realised that we had the chance to do whatever we wanted for a fairly captive audience. Why hold back?</p><p> “We&#39;ve made the album we wanted to make, and we&#39;ve made a pop album. We&#39;ve gone harder on the hooks and we&#39;ve crafted better songs.”</p><h3> <strong>It&#39;s a Trojan horse of left hooks. There&#39;s a moment on &#39;Down By The Stream&#39; where you&#39;re apologising for picking on a lad in your youth. Where does that come from?</strong></h3><p> “That was written with a stream of consciousness and I pulled apart my past. If I was going to write an album that framed me as struggling, then I wanted to flesh out my character. It&#39;s a heightened version of me, but it is me. I wanted to remind myself and other people that I&#39;m flawed as well and have done things that I shouldn&#39;t have done. That alludes to the fear that I have and everyone else has and it manifests itself in darker ways that aren&#39;t on. It was a long time ago and I learned from it.” </p><figure id="attachment_3139751" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3139751" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3139751" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME.jpg" alt="庭院法" width="2000" height="1269" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME-1392x883.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Yard-Act-Credit-Phoebe-Fox-for-NME-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3139751" class="wp-caption-text"> Yard Act. CREDIT: Phoebe Fox for NME</figcaption></figure><h3> <strong><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/katy-j-pearson">Katy J Pearson</a> lends some beautiful vocals to &#39;When The Laughter Stops&#39;. What does she bring to the vibe of the album?</strong></h3><p> “We&#39;ve collaborated with Katy live a few times and we did a remix of her song &#39;Miracle&#39; a while back. Whenever we found ourselves on the same festival bill, she&#39;s joined us for covers and stuff on stage. We came out around a similar time and we just get on and always said we&#39;d do something. We had this song with this hook that I just couldn&#39;t quite hit right, and we all agreed that Katy would be the best person for it.</p><p> “I&#39;ve been a fan of Katy since the start. It was a pleasure and privilege to finally get to work with her, and she&#39;s lifted that track above and beyond.”</p><h3> <strong>Has all this self analysis changed the way you view ambition and what you want to do with Yard Act?</strong></h3><p> “Yeah. We&#39;re all in, obviously, but we&#39;re creatively aware of what we have. It&#39;s not something we want to lose by turning it into a job that crushes us. The world is still open to us at the moment and we&#39;re all very keen to see how far we can take it on our terms. We&#39;re here if people want us. We&#39;re already working on album three. If anything starts to dry up, then we won&#39;t force it. The last thing any of us want is to tour into diminishing returns because &#39;it&#39;s a job now&#39;, though it would break my heart to give it up. Although that&#39;s a way off… at least a year, I think.</p><p> “We&#39;ve been producing different artists, which is interesting and exciting because there are four of us and we work collectively on that. We&#39;ve been working on a film that I&#39;ve been writing with James Slater who does all of our videos, which is all based around Yard Act. If we can get the funding for that, then that would be great. I want to be free to do what I want to do, to quote whatever <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/primal-scream">Primal Scream</a> sample that was. For the next 18 months we&#39;ll just be touring like motherfuckers because there&#39;s still work to be done.”</p><h3> <strong>And you&#39;re ready for it?</strong></h3><p> “I&#39;ve found a love for touring that I lost. On the song &#39;Petroleum&#39; I talk about a gig where I threw it all away. That was completely on me, but I was at a point where I was so depleted. I can forgive myself for that now, but I still feel the shame because performing live is sacred and there&#39;s a responsibility in being on the stage. You have to give yourself fully to performance. A combination of things has meant I&#39;m back in love with playing live. I&#39;ve figured out how we can sustain this energy. That&#39;s largely down to how we&#39;re playing together now. We&#39;re going to playing a lot and we&#39;re going to be enjoying it.”</p><h3> <strong>There are some big venues on the UK tour – are arenas calling next?</strong></h3><p> “If arenas become a thing, then I would be well up for seeing if we could it in a way that works for us. I wouldn&#39;t feel defeated if it didn&#39;t translate to that point. Life&#39;s too short to have pre-determined, set-in-stone ideas about what is and isn&#39;t going to work. I&#39;ve got no shame in falling flat on my face at this stage. If someone said, &#39;On album three, you can play Leeds Arena&#39;, then I absolutely would. If it half sold out and we sounded crap, I&#39;d just go back to playing smaller rooms and be happy again. I&#39;d definitely try it. Why wouldn&#39;t we? I&#39;ve seen amazing arena shows. How do I be <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kendrick-lamar">Kendrick Lamar</a> at Madison Square Garden, and make that work by us being Yard Act. You never know if you don&#39;t try it. So, &#39;Yes we will be playing Leeds Arena in 2025&#39; is what I&#39;m saying!” </p><p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-3520648 size-full" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000.jpg" alt="Yard Act announce second album, 'Where's My Utopia?'" width="1500" height="1500" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000.jpg 1500w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000-400x400.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000-800x800.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000-696x696.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000-1392x1392.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/yard_Act_utopia_2000-1068x1068.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></p><p> Yard Act release &#39;Where&#39;s My Utopia?&#39; on March 1, 2024. Pre-order it <a href="